<section xml:id="browser-preferences" version="5.0" xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"
                                               xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"
                                               xmlns:xl="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" >
  <title>Browser preferences</title>
  <anchor role="helpid" condition="editorPrefPageContextId" xml:id="browser-preferences.browserPrefPageContextId" xreflabel="Browser Preferences"/>
  <para>
    In the <emphasis>Test - Browsers</emphasis> preferences,
    you can alter your preferences for:
  </para>
  <variablelist>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>
        Filter coloring 
      </term>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          Here you can configure if you want the background of a browser to be
          colored when the filter is active. This helps to remind you that
          a filter is active and not all components are shown.
          The used background color can be changed as well.
        </para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
  </variablelist>
</section>